Certainly! Here's a list of ethical hacking tools along with their purposes and official websites:

Reconnaissance & Information Gathering

1. Nmap – Network scanning and mapping
Official website: nmap.org


2. Recon-ng – Web reconnaissance
Official website: github.com/lanmaster53/recon-ng


3. Shodan – Search engine for internet-connected devices
Official website: shodan.io


4. theHarvester – Collects emails, subdomains, and names
Official website: github.com/laramies/theHarvester


5. Maltego – Open-source intelligence (OSINT) visualization
Official website: maltego.com



Vulnerability Assessment & Exploitation

6. Metasploit – Penetration testing framework
Official website: metasploit.com


7. OpenVAS – Vulnerability scanner
Official website: openvas.org


8. Nessus – Security vulnerability scanning
Official website: tenable.com/products/nessus


9. Burp Suite – Web security testing
Official website: portswigger.net/burp


10. Nikto – Web server scanner
Official website: cirt.net/Nikto2



Password Cracking & Brute-Forcing

11. John the Ripper – Password cracking
Official website: openwall.com/john/


12. Hashcat – GPU-based password recovery
Official website: hashcat.net


13. Hydra – Online password brute-forcing
Official website: github.com/vanhauser-thc/thc-hydra


14. Medusa – Network login brute-forcer
Official website: foofus.net/goons/jmk/medusa/medusa.html



Wireless Network Testing

15. Aircrack-ng – Wi-Fi security auditing
Official website: aircrack-ng.org


16. Kismet – Wireless network sniffer
Official website: kismetwireless.net


17. Reaver – WPA2 WPS brute-force attack
Official website: github.com/t6x/reaver-wps-fork-t6x


18. Fern Wi-Fi Cracker – Wireless penetration testing
Official website: github.com/savio-code/fern-wifi-cracker



Web Security & Exploitation

19. SQLmap – Automated SQL injection testing
Official website: sqlmap.org


20. XSSer – Detects and exploits XSS vulnerabilities
Official website: xsser.03c8.net


21. Wapiti – Web application vulnerability scanner
Official website: wapiti.sourceforge.io



Packet Sniffing & Traffic Analysis

22. Wireshark – Network protocol analyzer
Official website: wireshark.org


23. tcpdump – Packet capturing tool
Official website: tcpdump.org


24. Ettercap – Man-in-the-middle attack tool
Official website: ettercap-project.org



Forensics & Malware Analysis

25. Autopsy – Digital forensics platform
Official website: sleuthkit.org/autopsy/


26. Volatility – Memory forensics analysis
Official website: volatilityfoundation.org


27. YARA – Malware classification and detection
Official website: virustotal.github.io/yara/



Social Engineering & Phishing

28. Social-Engineer Toolkit (SET) – Simulates social engineering attacks
Official website: github.com/trustedsec/social-engineer-toolkit


29. Evilginx2 – Phishing tool for bypassing 2FA
Official website: github.com/kgretzky/evilginx2



Anonymity & Privacy

30. Tor – Anonymous web browsing
Official website: torproject.org


31. ProxyChains – Hides IP addresses with proxy chaining
Official website: github.com/haad/proxychains


32. OpenVPN – Encrypts internet traffic
Official website



